## 3. ESTRUTURA DO HOOK REGISTRY (NCHKFR001hookregistry.py)

### 3.1 Formato YAML de Regras

```yaml
hooks:
  - event: tool_called
    matcher:
      tool_type: Edit|Write|MultiEdit
      file_pattern: "**/server.py|**/sub_server.py"
    script: .nc/hooks/lockguard.py
    action: block
    description: "Bloqueia edio de arquivos @LOCK"

  - event: file_written
    matcher:
      file_pattern: "**/*.mdc|**/*.md"
    script: .nc/hooks/ssotupdate.py
    action: log
    description: "Atualiza SSOT aps escrita de lobe/doc"

  - event: bash_executed
    matcher:
      command_pattern: "rm \-rf|mkfs|dd"
    script: .nc/hooks/destructivecommandalert.py
    action: warn
    description: "Alerta para comandos destrutivos"
```

### 3.2 Script Python de Hook (exemplo lockguard.py)

```python
#!/usr/bin/env python3
import sys
import json
import os

context = json.loads(sys.stdin.read())
file_path = context.get("filePath", "")

# Lista de arquivos @LOCK (pode vir de SSOT)
LOCK_FILES = ["server.py", "sub_server.py", "NCNAMFR001namingregistry.yaml"]

if any(lock_file in file_path for lock_file in LOCK_FILES):
    print(json.dumps({
        "block": True,
        "reason": f"Arquivo {file_path} est protegido por @LOCK",
        "suggestion": "Use atomic lock override se necessrio"
    }))
    sys.exit(1)

print(json.dumps({"block": False}))
```

### 3.3 Integrao com Mentor Mode

- **MentorHooks** rodam **antes** do Mentor Mode? No  so complementares:
  - Mentor Mode opera no **nvel do prompt LLM** (injetando contexto).
  - MentorHooks operam no **nvel da tool** (validando a ao concreta).
- **Ordem ideal:** MentorHooks (tool validation)  Mentor Mode (context injection)  LLM  Tool execution  GuardHooks (audit).

